05/05/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The three Adriatic Charter states -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- signed a Memorandum of Understanding in Brussels Wednesday (4 May) on the deployment of a multinational medical unit to Afghanistan. The document was signed by the defence ministers of the three countries -- Albania's Pandeli Majko, Croatia's Berislav Roncevic and Macedonia's Jovan Manasijevski -- as well as by NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer. The joint medical team would serve as part of the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan. Representatives of the countries also adopted a statement marking the second anniversary of the Adriatic Charter. (Albanian News - 05/05/05; NATO Web site, Makfax - 04/05/05)
